### Configure basic Playwright test options in JavaScript

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-configuration-js.md

Use `defineConfig` to set up fundamental test runner options such as `testDir`, `fullyParallel`, `retries`, `reporter`, `baseURL`, and `projects` for different browsers.

```js
import { defineConfig, devices } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  // Look for test files in the "tests" directory, relative to this configuration file.
  testDir: 'tests',

  // Run all tests in parallel.
  fullyParallel: true,

  // Fail the build on CI if you accidentally left test.only in the source code.
  forbidOnly: !!process.env.CI,

  // Retry on CI only.
  retries: process.env.CI ? 2 : 0,

  // Opt out of parallel tests on CI.
  workers: process.env.CI ? 1 : undefined,

  // Reporter to use
  reporter: 'html',

  use: {
    // Base URL to use in actions like `await page.goto('/')`.
    baseURL: 'http://localhost:3000',

    // Collect trace when retrying the failed test.
    trace: 'on-first-retry',
  },
  // Configure projects for major browsers.
  projects: [
    {
      name: 'chromium',
      use: { ...devices['Desktop Chrome'] },
    },
  ],
  // Run your local dev server before starting the tests.
  webServer: {
    command: 'npm run start',
    url: 'http://localhost:3000',
    reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,
  },
});
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Playwright Projects for Multiple Browsers

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/best-practices-js.md

Set up projects in `playwright.config.ts` to run tests across different browsers like Chromium, Firefox, and WebKit, ensuring broad compatibility for your application.

```typescript
import { defineConfig, devices } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  projects: [
    {
      name: 'chromium',
      use: { ...devices['Desktop Chrome'] },
    },
    {
      name: 'firefox',
      use: { ...devices['Desktop Firefox'] },
    },
    {
      name: 'webkit',
      use: { ...devices['Desktop Safari'] },
    }
  ]
});
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Playwright with Multiple Web Servers

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-webserver-js.md

This configuration shows how to launch multiple local development servers simultaneously by providing an array of `webServer` configurations. This is useful for testing applications with separate frontend and backend services.

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  webServer: [
    {
      command: 'npm run start',
      url: 'http://localhost:3000',
      name: 'Frontend',
      timeout: 120 * 1000,
      reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,
    },
    {
      command: 'npm run backend',
      url: 'http://localhost:3333',
      name: 'Backend',
      timeout: 120 * 1000,
      reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,
    }
  ],
  use: {
    baseURL: 'http://localhost:3000',
  },
});
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Playwright with a Single Web Server and Base URL

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-webserver-js.md

Use this configuration to launch a single local development server before tests start and set a `baseURL`. This allows tests to use relative URLs for navigation, routing, and waiting methods, resolving them against the specified base URL.

```typescript
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  // Rest of your config...

  // Run your local dev server before starting the tests
  webServer: {
    command: 'npm run start',
    url: 'http://localhost:3000',
    reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,
  },
  use: {
    baseURL: 'http://localhost:3000',
  },
});
```

--------------------------------

### Use Playwright web-first locators

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/README.md

Examples of Playwright's resilient locators that find elements based on their user-facing attributes like role, label, placeholder, or test ID.

```TypeScript
page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' })
page.getByLabel('Email')
page.getByPlaceholder('Search...')
page.getByTestId('login-form')
```

